A17. Discover 10 different types of locks in use.
Turn knob lock = A type of locking mechanism that allows a door to be secured from the inside without using a key by rotate a knob or lever to engage or disengage the locking mechanism.
Slide lock = A simple lock where a metal bolt or bar slides into a catch to secure a door, gate, or window. It is easy to operate from one side.
pin tumbler lock = Uses a key to align a series of pins inside a cylinder so that the lock can turn and either engage or release the latch.
QR code login = Some application uses a QR code to login into new device. By scaning QR code on the new device with app in the old device you will be able to login to your new device.
Token = Some website will send token out to your email or number to ensure that you are the owner of that email/number.
Touch to lock/open = Some public washroom in Perth have this lock system where you can touch to open, close, or lock the door.
Email and password = Before you login to your account a lot of website will ask you to enter email and password login.
I am not a robot security = It can come in many form, from just click a button to solve a confusing puzzles, but all of them have one identical feature. They try to filter and locked AI/bot out of there system.
Chain/cable lock = The owner put chain or cable around a an object and lock it onto something, the only way to take the chain out is to unlock or cut it.
A push-button door knob lock = a type of turn/knob lock where a small button on the knob is pressed to lock the door from the inside.
